subSubSection.paragraph:
Description. Holotype . Female (
Figs 1 –3, 6– 8
). Body length 4.1 mm ; fore wing length 2.4 mm ; antenna length 2.1 mm .

Head. Head in dorsal view subquadrate ( 30 : 29 ), narrower than width of mesosoma ( 54 : 62 ), with extremely prominent antennal shelf (
Fig. 1
); in lateral view as long as high. Frons, face, genae and vertex with scattered setigerous punctures, which denser on face (
Fig. 3
). Tentorial pit distinctly developed, not large. Malar sulcus rudimentary, very shallow. Clypeus transverse ( 18 : 13 ), semicircular, convex. Epistomal sulcus distinct. Ratio of pleurostomal distance to width of head 16 : 30 (
Fig. 3
). Mandible long, bidentate with upper tooth shorter than lower tooth. Eye height shorter than half head height ( 11 : 24 ), and distinctly longer than malar space ( 15 : 9 ); eye with long setae and surrounded by semicircular groove. Ocelli large (
Fig. 1
); LOL equal to diameter of anterior ocellus; POL longer than OOL ( 4 : 3 ). Occipital flange broad and smooth, with several long setae medially (
Fig. 1
). Postgenal cushion dense ( Figs 3, 6 ).

